<div class="content_text">

   <p>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Since its inception period (july 2002) WSC has been implementing microfinance program as its major component. WSC has followed the Grameen Bank Model Propounded by Nobel laureate Prof. Muhammad Yunus of Bangladesh. The aim of the program is to uplift the socio-economic conditions of the poor women. By August, 2011 over 8000 poor women of Kathmandu District have been benifited from this program. The number of women involve in the program is increasing gradually both at rular and urban areas. In total 371 Women Support microfinance centers have been established in 29 VDCs and two Metropolitan Cities. Microfinance program is operating through five contact offices.</br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Due to the low income level and poor lifestyle of women,women have faced different types of social discrimination not only in nepal but also in the world.Because of the lack of parental property right to daughters,they do not posses land and house.They can not borrow loan from the bank or financial institution because financial institution needs collateral in terms of asset like land and house to borrow loan.So WSC provides microfinance services in the door steps of poor women to uplift their socio-economic status with group collateral.

   </p>
