<div class="objective_text">
    <h2>Group Saving</h2>
       <p>When women becomes member of the organization they have to deposit
					allocated amount of compulsory saving every fortnight.They can withdraw
					the amount when the member leaves the organization. WSC provides interest
					according to organization rule.Depositor deposit small amount in installment
					basis, when they leave the organization they get large amount. In this way, it
					seems to be a small amount. WSC has collected Rs. 20.90 million in FY 2067/068. It can be 						said that drops makes an ocean.
				</p>
    <h2>Pesonal Saving</h2>
       <p>According to members need they can deposit or withdraw their savings at any time.
					These types of saving are categorized as personal savings. The Organization provides 8.0 percent interest on this saving products. Personel depositor can withdraw their personal saving whenever they need to pay loan installment repayment or other expenses. In this way total amount of personal savings till F/Y 2067/068 is Rs. 13.60 million.
				</p>

			<h2>Yojana Saving (Plan Saving)</h2>
			  <p>Considering the members future security, WSC has manage this kind of saving called Yojana savings. These types of savings have long term vision and it is different from other saving products. This type of product is like a pension saving. In this product members can deposit same amount of money in every center meeting for 10 or 15 years. When members reach the maturity period of 10 years.They can get one and half amount of the their deposited money. This scheme is just to attract members for retaining long period in the organization.If some one wants to leave the center, she can get 5.0 percent interest on their deposit. It is a compulsory saving scheme but the amount they diposited is volunteer. From this saving they can get contigent loan.
				</p>
      <h2>Upakar Kosh</h2>
        <p>All the penalties, donations, prizes and other funds are kept on this Kosh(fund). This
					kosh is used according to the decision of the center meeting. For example they can purchase mat, register etc. Up to this F/Y 2067/068 Rs. 4.5 lakh Upkar kosh has been collected.
				</p>



